Output: 
NAME                HOST/PORT                                                        PATH   SERVICES   PORT   TERMINATION     WILDCARD
eda-webhook-route   eda-webhook-route-ansible-automation-platform.apps-crc.testing          mysvc      5000   edge/Redirect   None


Use it in curl, something like
curl -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
     -X POST \
     -k \
     -d '{"i": 1, "message": "Testing webhook"}' \
     https://eda-webhook-route-ansible-automation-platform.apps-crc.testing/endpoint
or, may be
curl ... https://eda-webhook-route-ansible-automation-platform.apps-crc.testing/

The first one with /endpoint seems to be the correct one. It looks curl was successful, but I could not find the message in the rulebook of 
"System is working with a Vengeance!!!"
