Finally, finally, I did get "System is working with a Vengeance!!!" in the AAP GUI console, for the Running "NotSimple" rulebook correspoding to file test_simple1.yml and for the curl mentioned above. It looks an additional entry in /etc/hosts file of eda-webhook-route-ansible-automation-platform.apps-crc.testing is added by the whole process. Also eda-route1.yml stands validated.

This test was important, as it ties the AAP configuration and OpenShift configuration.
If AAP installed in OpenShift cause any more problem, we might shift to standalone AAP for more work. I wished the eda-route1.yml to be validated if I need to abandon OpenShift deploy of AAP. That was achieved.

